= Ronan

Ronan served as the founding chief technology officer of the original Earth company. He led much of the technical work behind the first discoveries. He took a government role after the withdrawal.

Ronan helped move key systems and preserve the research during withdrawal. He then helped create institutions that removed technology from founder control. Those institutions spread his former authority across public bodies built to outlive him.
